  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was no force which could change that what Schindler decided.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He decided to be with us all the time, until the end.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had, of course, a position in circles.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was even twice arrested.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he had a strong contract with Berlin, and he was always made free.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we believed in his word, without any hesitation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was time after the war that we said, if we can believe in God, our God was Schindler.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I think his bringing up in his family was of that sort.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What-- they say you have to love your neighbor like you love yourself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he understood that German-- Germany has done a great [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] mistake starting with the Jewish Final Solution.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was a very [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] difficult thing that they undertook.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, Eichmann was the head of that, Final Solution.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Eventually, he was caught up after the war and brought to the court in Israel and punished by hanging.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First of all, we have seen that on the railway we have seen a lot of transport with the Red Cross, with injured people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we found that the same wagon which we left yesterday to the left, they came back to the right, because they were limiting their expansion.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we knew that something is wrong, after all, the radio give us the information.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had no other way, because the newspaper didn't come to us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I will tell you the truth, that it was rather a London, a famous London Voice of, of-- but there was also Voice of America, of course.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
